            Represents a dynamic object that allows access to all properties and methods of the wrapped object as if they were , regardless of their actual access level.

Note that all dynamically retrieved members are also instances of  to allow for further dynamic access. The only value explicitly propagated to allow ?.  propagation is . This does not work directly on an object of type , i.e. the following method invocation will always take place:

